Jürgens also had his own opinion on the criticism of the noise of birds: "There is a lot of communication, they have a lot to say."
The intelligence and dexterity of the animals are legendary: Rooks not only use tools to get a treat, but they even make their own tools.
Behavioural researchers at Cambridge University recently tested the intelligence of birds on four rooks.
