Patti LaBelle indicted for allegedly forcing an infant to vomit out of fear
A New York family claims that the disco in the lobby of their Manhattan building, Patti LaBelle, has had a fit of addiction that has scared her little daughter so much that she vomited in fear.
The tirade of the "Lady Marmalade" singer made the 18-month-old Genevieve Monk so afraid that she suffered from "personality changes, sleep disturbances" and "increased fear of strangers", her family told the Supreme Court in Manhattan.
