There are slogans about China, Iran and Israel, often unsubstantiated.
Mitt Romney, who was the most popular in appointing the "Grand Old Party", threatened to quote the Chinese at the WTO, accusing them of "currency manipulation" - the leading issue in an America that is highly irritated by the migration of entire industries to Asia.
Stupid if this is to imply launching a trade war, he said.
Jon Huntsman, Obama ’ s former ambassador to China and the only candidate who seems to have a mature vision of foreign policy, has almost confined himself to his emotionally flattering behavior.
