They recall that Obama, too, was an amateur and had to add water to his wine when it came to anti-terror.
They rightly insist on the failure of his naïve dialogue with Iran, the hasty departure of his "boys" from Iraq, his indecision in Libya, which also earned him the reputation of weakness.
